oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Fess Parker with Mr. Schmidt at a Nashville event, 1955 May
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Pictured left to right: Mr. Schmidt shaking hands with the celebrity television star Fess Parker, at a special event in Nashville, Tennessee circa May 1955. Fess Elisha Parker, Jr. (August 16, 1924 - March 18, 2010) was an American film and television actor best known for his portrayals of the frontiersmen Davy Crockett and Daniel Boone during the 1950s and 1960s. Forms part of Record Group 3, Metro Davidson County Photographer. 1 photograph negative : b & w ; 4 x 5 in.
